    "description": "Single ventricle defects are a group of congenital heart conditions that result in the heart having only one functioning ventricle instead of the typical two. This condition significantly affects the blood flow within the heart and the oxygenation of blood. Patients with single ventricle defects often require multidisciplinary care and a series of surgeries throughout their life to manage the condition. The severity of symptoms can vary depending on the specific anatomy and associated defects.",
    "symptoms": [
      {
        "symptom": "Cyanosis",
        "description": "A bluish discoloration of the skin, lips, and nails due to insufficient oxygen in the blood."
      },
